

=Context=

This page is originally inspired by the Fourthsector.net's page outlining a [http://www.fourthsector.net/learn/supportive-ecosystem/ Supportive Ecosystem] for the [[Fourth Sector]], which consists of a new type of market entities which can blend  for-profit and not-for-profit practices based on concepts of [[Blended Value]], [[Shared Value]], etc ..

The limitations of the Fourth Sector approach, from a more strict 'P2P' point of view, is that such entities are not per se engaged in [[Peer Production]], which requires the sharing of knowledge, code, or designs in a [[Commons]]; amongst other requirements. Their approach is also U.S.-centric.

Nevertheless, Fourth Sector organizations could be the privileged form that commons-friendly enterprises can take, since the lack of the sole drive for profit maximisation, makes them more likely to respect the logic of the commons.



